177
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:48,242
No, I just stepped on the gas. That's all.

178
00:08:50,775 --> 00:08:53,859
I never imagined pushing a car could be so much fun.

179
00:08:53,859 --> 00:08:56,409
- Fun?
- Yes.

180
00:08:58,525 --> 00:09:00,200
Let's sit down.

181
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:11,409
Speaking of resting,

182
00:09:12,483 --> 00:09:15,010
Chen Da Wu told me yesterday

183
00:09:15,010 --> 00:09:18,400
that resting isn't for a longer journey.

184
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,659
Resting is just for the sake of resting.

185
00:09:22,192 --> 00:09:23,909
Seems like it's true.

186
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:28,252
Anyway, it's too late to attend Da Wu's seminar now.

187
00:09:28,252 --> 00:09:30,399
I'll apologize to him tomorrow.

188
00:09:30,399 --> 00:09:32,951
For now, let's just rest well.

189
00:09:35,650 --> 00:09:37,659
Let's not waste the day either.

190
00:09:38,417 --> 00:09:40,159
What do you want to do?

191
00:09:42,067 --> 00:09:44,318
Anywhere is fine.

192
00:09:44,318 --> 00:09:46,692
But I feel like our carefree trip

193
00:09:46,692 --> 00:09:49,199
is missing one important member.

194
00:10:18,359 --> 00:10:19,681
You're back.

195
00:10:19,681 --> 00:10:21,984
Grandma, is the inspection over?

196
00:10:21,984 --> 00:10:24,192
It's all done and it went smoothly.

197
00:10:24,192 --> 00:10:26,017
How was Da Wu's seminar?

198
00:10:26,017 --> 00:10:27,432
We didn't make it.

199
00:10:27,432 --> 00:10:30,059
Grandma, we're heading out in 30 minutes.

200
00:10:30,059 --> 00:10:31,951
Where are we going?

201
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:39,109
When will the other celebrities arrive in Kinmen?

202
00:10:39,109 --> 00:10:40,192
Probably early tomorrow morning.

203
00:10:40,192 --> 00:10:42,276
But they haven't signed the contract yet.

204
00:10:42,276 --> 00:10:44,158
I've talked to their agents.

205
00:10:44,158 --> 00:10:46,866
They'll sign it when they arrive tomorrow.

206
00:10:46,866 --> 00:10:48,498
Director and producer.

207
00:10:48,498 --> 00:10:50,399
Sorry.

208
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:51,817
Welcome to Kinmen.

209
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:53,640
And you are?

210
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:54,815
I'm from Kinmen.

211
00:10:54,815 --> 00:10:57,125
I'm also the executive agent for Bai Yin Mo,

212
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:58,699
Hong Xiao Guang.

213
00:10:58,699 --> 00:10:59,900
Nice to meet you.

214
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:03,696
Executive agent. So, like an assistant?

215
00:11:03,696 --> 00:11:06,314
Yes, but I'm working for Bai Yin Mo.

216
00:11:06,314 --> 00:11:07,498
So, it's different.

217
00:11:07,498 --> 00:11:09,034
See you tomorrow.

218
00:11:11,067 --> 00:11:12,234
When will the car arrive?

219
00:11:12,234 --> 00:11:13,318
It's over there.

220
00:11:13,318 --> 00:11:15,034
All right.

221
00:11:16,399 --> 00:11:17,734
Lily, I've just arrived in Kinmen

222
00:11:17,734 --> 00:11:20,399
and I greeted the director and everyone.

223
00:11:20,399 --> 00:11:21,607
I'm going to find Yin Mo now.

224
00:11:21,607 --> 00:11:23,242
We'll stay in touch.

225
00:11:37,313 --> 00:11:38,937
What's wrong?

226
00:11:48,052 --> 00:11:49,067
I get it.

227
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:51,199
You don't know where to go, do you?

228
00:11:53,498 --> 00:11:55,359
I get it.

229
00:11:55,359 --> 00:11:57,732
In the past, everything was always arranged for you.

230
00:11:57,732 --> 00:11:59,399
Now that you're suddenly on your own,

231
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:01,199
you're unsure where to go.

232
00:12:02,531 --> 00:12:04,840
It's okay. Take your time.

233
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:08,831
We have plenty of time and plenty of gas.

234
00:12:08,831 --> 00:12:10,200
Yes.

235
00:12:17,775 --> 00:12:21,730
It's a carefree trip. Turn off the phone.

236
00:12:21,730 --> 00:12:23,125
I'll turn mine off, too.

237
00:12:23,125 --> 00:12:24,659
Me, too.

238
00:12:26,399 --> 00:12:29,557
All right. With all our phones off, we can truly relax now.

239
00:12:29,557 --> 00:12:32,597
Whether you want to go forward or backward,

240
00:12:32,597 --> 00:12:34,399
you're free to go wherever you wish.

241
00:12:34,399 --> 00:12:35,734
This isn't the way.

242
00:12:35,734 --> 00:12:38,409
You need to make a U-turn.

243
00:13:06,598 --> 00:13:08,200
You keep playing that.

244
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:11,200
You scared my grandma.

245
00:13:13,692 --> 00:13:14,906
They're fishing over there.

246
00:13:14,906 --> 00:13:16,324
Wouldn't they be startled?

247
00:13:16,324 --> 00:13:17,450
Hello.

248
00:13:17,450 --> 00:13:19,524
Hi.

249
00:13:19,524 --> 00:13:21,118
Hey.

250
00:13:36,491 --> 00:13:39,159
Do people still go to such barbershops?

251
00:13:40,597 --> 00:13:41,899
Before you came to Kinmen,

252
00:13:41,899 --> 00:13:44,184
I brought my grandma here for a makeover.

253
00:13:44,184 --> 00:13:49,283
Yes, I even got a perm to welcome a superstar.

254
00:13:53,285 --> 00:13:56,252
The latest trend, root perm.

255
00:14:02,531 --> 00:14:03,899
All right. Ready.

256
00:14:03,899 --> 00:14:06,492
Three, two, one!

257
00:14:10,317 --> 00:14:11,909
Got it.

258
00:14:12,907 --> 00:14:15,083
- Hi.
- Da Wu.

259
00:14:15,999 --> 00:14:17,663
Hi.

260
00:14:17,663 --> 00:14:18,696
Xu Man is here, too.

261
00:14:18,696 --> 00:14:21,203
- Xu Man, sit here.
- No need.

262
00:14:21,203 --> 00:14:23,057
I'm just here to say hi.

263
00:14:23,057 --> 00:14:25,131
I made a few new versions of that drink from before.

264
00:14:25,131 --> 00:14:26,822
Come try them sometime.

265
00:14:26,822 --> 00:14:28,516
Sure. Thank you.

266
00:14:28,516 --> 00:14:30,729
I'll be off then.

267
00:14:30,729 --> 00:14:32,072
